	<div id="discussion-comments">
	
		
			<ul class="comment b2" id="comment-7710371">
				
				<li class="comment-author" >
                    
                        <div class="badges">
                            
                                



                            
                        </div>
                        <div class="profile" >
                            
                                

<img class="author-profile-picture" src="http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/discussion/avatars/2010/08/23/YummieMummie/98ebdad5-cd33-4ee6-9f59-d9a134012195/60x60.png" height="60" width="60" alt="" />
<a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/discussion/user/YummieMummie" title="User profile page">YummieMummie</a>

                            
                            <p class="date">19 September 2010 12:26AM</p>
                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>Mmm maybe but I am a lot more muscley/toned through exercise (I do a combination of running/cross training and weights) and that may mean that although your weight doesn't go down, but you do look better and thinner as a result. When I was my thinnest size 6-8 I was eating a lot less but I wasn't "starved". I didn't go to the gym, but I did walk a lot. I'm a 10 now so I am probably a much healthier weight. I prefer the hourglass curvy Beyonce type physique to a stick insect look. I think articles like this put people off exercise but they aren't taking into account that muscle weighs more than fat, and that exercise tones your body and builds core strength/stability. All important for a healthy lifestyle.</p>
						
					</div>
				</li>
				
