					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>I was told something similar to this years ago, and in fact it is self-evident if you observe the calorie counters attached to gym equipment - they tick by rather slowly!</p><p>Even after a fairly short period of gym membership, however, I have more muscle, and my metabolism seems to have got much faster as a result. Is it not true that the more muscle mass you have, the more calories you burn simply sitting still?</p><p>If the only benefit of exercise was feeling better and having a body that you are more comfortable with, I'm quite sure that many if not most of us who presently go to 'all that effort' would continue to do so. </p><p>As a rather skinny teacher who never sits still, it was never my intention to lose weight at the gym in any case, so I'm perhaps not qualified to comment on the cases of people who really struggle. They have my sympathy, as I tuck into a slab of cake!</p>
						
