							<p>I thought it was dangerous when Time Magazine did a story with the exact same headline, and I think it's still dangerous.</p><p>http://taoofbachelorhood.com/2009/08/11/why-the-media-wont-make-you-thin/</p><p>The implication of the premise (people, sadly, don't read entire articles nowadays), that exercise doesn't help in a sensible weight-loss program, is dead wrong, and most of the experts you've quoted, if confronted with that fact, will have to agree. Studies that only tangentially fit their square pegs into this round hole will make people think there's science to the headline, but in reality the fact is that given two people eat the same way, the one who exercises, wins. </p><p>And the couch potato is on the losing end every time.</p>
						
