							<p>Articles like this make me mad.  </p><p>So the relation ship between exercise and weight loss isn't so simple as exercise = weight loss, but the title is short and snappy enough to capture the attention of the overweight and obese section of our society - many of whom probably won't have the staying power to read the article through and find out that's not exactly what you mean or even what the article says.  It's wilful deception, and for who's gain might I add?</p><p>Losing weight is like everything in life - it's a choice.  If you want anything in life bad enough you'll find a way to make it happen.  It's called willpower, or motivation if you like.  Anyone can lose weight.  They just have to decide to and find a way to make it happen.</p><p>If someone can't lose weight it's either because they don't want to enough, aren't trying hard enough or are relying on someone else to do it for them.  Simple.</p>
						
