							<p>I'd rather do the exercise. I feel crap when I eat fewer calories and crap when I don't exercise, so put those together and... bad. The maths might add up in favour of eating less but that's not taking into account the higher energy levels you get from exercise which spur you onto doing more. Plus I find that when I exercise, the more aware I am of my body and so the more I want to treat it well with decent nutrition etc. I find adopting an attitude of restriction depressing and being active easier to maintain than cutting out calories. Better a motto of: "move more, eat better" than "don't move, eat less".</p><p><b>Jackanapes </b><br>My experience too.</p>
						
