					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>The problem is that the word exercise has negative connotations in many people minds (think: grim painful joyless self-obsessed goal-oriented treadmill etc.), so that when they read or are told they should exercise more, they find all sorts of reasons not to do so. The rather unfortunate headline and opening sections of this article now provide them with further ammunition.</p><p>But exercise is just moving your body - and moving your body frequently in the fresh air is energizing and fun. Going for a long walk, riding a bike, swimming, gardening: How could you not enjoy these things? Heck, even the weekly shop is exercise with all that bending, pushing, carrying. </p><p>Maybe the potatoes could be induced from their couches if they associated the word exercise with the pleasure of vitality and movement rather than with a grim determination to lose weight.</p>
						
