							<p>Burn more calories than you consume and watch the weight go. If your need is, say, 2000 calories a day, try living on 1200 until you have reached your desired weight. Then go back to 2000. I mention 2000 because that is the intake that maintains your weight. You wont lose or gain if you stick to that amount.</p><p>Exercise will make you feel great and is crucial for strengthening muscles to help protect your bones etc. However, unless you do silly amounts of exercise you have to combine it with a diet or you wont lose weight.</p>
						
