					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>This article, and most people who focus on weight loss misses the point, exercise is not about losing weight, its about feeling and being healthy, cardiovascular health will only come from exercise.</p><p>I've trained since I was at school, as I've played rugby since my teens, I'm now 48, but can still cycle 50 odd miles, I still play rugby for our 2nd team, even if these days I'm more likely to come off the bench. and to be honest, I'm my weight if anything has stayed roughly the same - I'm around 16.5 stones. I don't tend to focus so much on weight but on my belt, if I can take two holes off my belt, then I'm doing well.</p><p>My partner competes in triathlon's and did her first Iron Man this year, she's no stick insect either.</p><p>The fixation with being thin is daft, you see some hideous scrawny creatures in the gym, who seem to believe being skin and bone is somehow attractive - We've all joked about the strange sub-species of bottle blonde with a massive head and stick thin body you see in the bling bars in the city centers - sorry, give me a healthy lass who plays sport and has got curves over these wraith like creatures any day.</p>
						
