					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>What's the point of this article.  There is no new relevant research on this subject.  Any dietician years ago would have told you that normal exercising does not burn up significant calories compared to a modern high-fat diet.  Neither is fad-dieting a solution.  Crash diets/ grapefruit/ high fat etc etc.  </p><p>If you want to loose weight see it as a three year project.  You do not need to 'diet'  but actually change your whole lifestyle.  Increased exercise boosts feeling of well-being.  Reduce or stop alcohol consumption.  Make small changes like no butter or margarine on bread.  Increase consumption of high-bulk/ low-calorie foods such as fruit and vegetables. </p><p>It really is common-sense, just as surely no-one needs to be told to stop eating fast-foods?</p>
						
					</div>
